(
  'The Economics of Pre-Engineered Buildings (PEBs)',
  'economics-pre-engineered-buildings-peb',
  'Analyzing the cost and time benefits of PEBs versus conventional structural steel for warehouses and factories.',
  '<h1>Optimizing the Frame</h1><p>When designing a new warehouse, logistics center, or factory, developers face a choice: conventional structural steel or a Pre-Engineered Building (PEB). While conventional steel uses standard hot-rolled sections throughout, PEBs utilize custom-fabricated built-up plates tailored exactly to the bending moments of the frame.</p><h2>Material Efficiency vs. Fabrication Cost</h2><p>Because a PEB frame tapers—being thickest at the eaves where stress is highest and thinnest at the base—it uses significantly less total steel tonnage (often 20-30% less). However, fabricating these custom tapered sections requires more labor and welding.</p><p>In the current market, where material costs often outweigh labor costs, PEBs offer a compelling economic advantage for large clear-span industrial structures.</p>',
  '/assets/project-5.jpg',
  'Sarah Jenkins',
  'Industry News',
  '5 min read'
),
(
  'Welding Automation: The Robotic Revolution',
  'welding-automation-robotic-revolution',
  'How robotic welding arms and automated beam lines are addressing the skilled labor shortage in fabrication.',
  '<h1>Machine Consistency</h1><p>The fabrication industry is facing a global shortage of highly skilled welders. To maintain production capacity and quality, Jazeerat Al Hadeed is heavily investing in robotic welding automation.</p><h2>The Submerged Arc Advantage</h2><p>While robots excel at repetitive tasks like welding base plates and cleats, our biggest efficiency gains have come from Automated Submerged Arc Welding (SAW) tractors used for splicing heavy built-up girders. SAW provides massive deposition rates, deep penetration, and a perfectly smooth, slag-free bead.</p><p>Automation does not replace our skilled welders; it frees them to focus on the complex, critical joints that require human intuition and dexterity.</p>',
  '/assets/project-6.jpg',
  'Khalid Ibrahim',
  'Technical Insights',
  '4 min read'
